column5: Nice looking catch! Braving the cold paid off well for you.
Great shots Fish Farmer. Thanks for putting it up. It gets me though the day.
Great to get out with friends and catch some beauties.
Excellent fish there, Glad you got some nice ones.  looks too cold for me :santa:L
nice fish, looks like it was worth braving those frigid temps!

Thanks for the replys guys. I should have mentioned what set up we used. I think I used 20 different deep running lures and the best set up was a purplish pink Reef Runner with a 1 once snap, 15Lb braid, running back 200' from the inline boards. 100' of water in the channel out from Keith's  Shoul. I did hear some better reports from weeks that we weren't there. I guess as my signature says.
Looks like a fun trip Dave, well done!
Good work! We saw you guys out there last weekend. Sunday was such a beauty day weather wise on the water, how nice was that eh? Till next year...
Great report, looks like a fun (cold) time
Dem is hawgs!  Hey Dave the sliders for my trailer are awesome.  Thanx
Great report on BOQ - Thanks for sharing your story.  I thought my Partners and I were the only 3 Amigos out there!!!!!!  David  aka  Superdad
